title: 'Pakistan should be listed as terrorist state': Kapil Sibal demands amendment in UAPA

author: JYOTIRMOY HALDER
description: GM Shyam Sundar's Chennai-based academy is making waves by producing elite chess prodigies, including India's 86th grandmaster Srihari LR and FIDE Junior World Champion Pranav V. Shyam's coaching emphasises character, structured training, and camaraderie, fostering a supportive environment where students thrive. Despite financial challenges and personal sacrifices, Shyam remains dedicated to nurturing champions and instilling valuable life lessons.
title: Rs 50k/month, countless sacrifices: India’s chess future in Chennai hut

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Donald Trump has accused Joe Biden's aides and the media of a 'cover-up' regarding Biden's mental state, following the release of audio recordings from his 2023 interview with Special Counsel Robert Hur. The audio reveals Biden struggling to recall key details, including the year Trump was elected and the death of his son, Beau.
title: 'You can't have a man in that condition': Trump rages at Biden cover-up

author: LAKSHIMA SAREEN
description: The Haryana Board of School Education (HBSE) will declare the Class 10th Result 2025 today, May 17, at 12:30 PM. Nearly 3 lakh students who appeared for the exams from February 28 to March 19 can access their results on bseh.org.in. Students can also check scores via SMS and DigiLocker. In 2024, the overall pass percentage was 95.
title: Haryana 10th results: How to check HBSE class 10 scorecards online at bseh.org

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Donald Trump, in a Fox News interview, hailed his Middle East tour as a major success, securing $2 trillion in investments and strengthening ties. He defended accepting a Boeing jet from Qatar, asserting it was for the US Air Force. Trump claimed his policies prevented Iran from acquiring nuclear weapons and that he de-escalated tensions between India and Pakistan.
title: From India–Pak ceasefire to $2 trillion deals and Qatari jet gift: What Trump said

author: etimes.in
description: Abhishek Malhan, of Bigg Boss OTT 2 fame, has criticized Rahul Vaidya for suggesting Virat Kohli blocked him on Instagram. Malhan believes Vaidya's claims are a publicity stunt, asserting Kohli is unlikely to even know Vaidya exists or have time to block him. He urged Vaidya to focus on his singing career instead of seeking attention through unnecessary controversy.
title: Abhishek Malhan supports Virat Kohli and condemns Rahul Vaidya

author: KAUTILYA SINGH
description: An air ambulance encountered an accident near the Kedarnath helipad around 11:50 am on Saturday when its tail struck the ground during landing. The incident occurred as the pilot attempted to land in an open field due to technical difficulties at the helipad. Fortunately, the pilot, doctor, and nursing staff escaped without injuries, and the DGCA will investigate the mishap.
title: Air ambulance crashes while landing at Kedarnath, narrow escape for pilot

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack and geopolitical tensions, Indian companies and consumers are increasingly boycotting Pakistan and its allies like Turkey and Azerbaijan. This includes trade restrictions, cancellation of contracts with Turkish firms, and a significant drop in travel bookings.
title: 'Big ban’ actions: How India is shunning Pak and its allies

author: MOHD DILSHAD
description: A 17-year-old Dalit girl was found dead, hanging from a tree in Mainpuri district after she went missing on her way to school. Her family has alleged murder, accusing her cousin and his friends. Police have detained two individuals for questioning and are awaiting the autopsy report to determine the cause of death.
title: Dalit girl found hanging from tree in UP; family alleges murder by cousin, his friends

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Mumbai Indians, after a slow start in IPL 2025, have turned their season around with six consecutive victories, propelling them into playoff contention. Sunil Gavaskar credits Hardik Pandya's calm leadership and the renewed support from Mumbai fans as key factors in the team's resurgence. Mumbai Indians will now face Delhi Capitals on May 21, followed by Punjab Kings on May 26 in their final league matches.
title: 'Hardik Pandya hasn't done that ... ': Gavaskar opens up

author: MANVIR SAINI
description: Devindera Singh Dhillon is arrested for allegedly spying for Pakistan. Dhillon, a student, is accused of sharing defense installation details. Investigation agencies are analyzing his electronic devices and financial transactions. He reportedly met Pakistani handlers via the Kartarpur corridor. This is the second such arrest in Haryana. Earlier, Nauman Ilahi was arrested on similar charges of sharing information with Pakistan.
title: Haryana student held in Kaithal for spying, sharing defence info with Pak

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Vice President Jagdeep Dhankhar lauded Operation Sindoor as India's most profound cross-border strike against terrorism, drawing parallels to the US operation that eliminated Osama bin Laden. He emphasized the precision of the strikes, targeting Jaish-e-Mohammed and Lashkar-e-Taiba strongholds across the International Border. This operation followed the deadly Pahalgam terror attack, prompting a firm response from Prime Minister Modi.
title: Operation Sindoor akin to Bin Laden killing: VP Dhankhar

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Amid escalating violence, Israeli strikes in Gaza have resulted in over 250 deaths since Thursday, exacerbating an already dire humanitarian crisis. Despite international appeals for a ceasefire, Israel continues its military operations, while a prolonged blockade has led to severe shortages of food, fuel, and medical supplies, pushing Gaza towards famine.
title: 'People are starving,' says Trump as Israeli strikes kill over 250 in Gaza in two days

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Following Operation Sindoor, the Centre has formed seven all-party delegations, led by figures like Shashi Tharoor and Ravi Shankar Prasad, to convey India's firm stance against terrorism to key partner nations. These delegations, comprising MPs from across the political spectrum, will visit countries in the Middle East, Africa, and Asia.
title: Ravi-led delegation to visit Saudi Arabia; Sule to visit Oman - Who is going where?

author: SANJIB CHAKRABARTY
description: Sheikh Farhad Mondal, an orchard owner, was arrested for allegedly killing Sudipto Pandit. Pandit was suspected of stealing mangoes. The incident occurred in Naihati. Mondal reportedly assaulted Pandit, leading to his death. Following the incident, a mob set fire to Mondal's property in Shibdaspur. Authorities deployed RAF and police to manage the unrest. The situation is now under control.
title: Teen beaten to death for 'picking mangoes'; mob torches orchard, house in Bengal

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Tesla's stock surged, increasing its market cap to $1.12 trillion, prompting Elon Musk to taunt Minnesota Governor Tim Walz on X. Musk referenced Walz's earlier mockery of Tesla's stock decline, responding with sarcasm and personal insults. Walz had previously joked about Tesla's struggles, leading to Musk's sharp rebuke and subsequent name-calling, before Walz walked back his comments.
title: Tesla stock jumps 45% in a month; Musk sends message to Tim Walk: Yo Timmy ...

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Off the coast of Hadera, Israel, a fatal shark attack, the first of its kind in the region, has ignited safety concerns. Dusky and Sandbar sharks, drawn to the warm waters near a power station, gather annually, attracting onlookers.
title: Watch: Humans swimming with sharks at Israeli beach causes concern

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Following the announcement of an all-party delegation to address Pakistan-sponsored terrorism, BJP criticized Congress for omitting Shashi Tharoor from their initial list. BJP leaders accused Rahul Gandhi of disliking party members who support India's position. The controversy arose after Congress proposed names like Syed Naseer Hussain, whose supporter allegedly raised pro-Pakistan slogans, sparking further debate.
title: ‘Why does Rahul hate those who speak for India?’ BJP slams Cong for excluding Tharoor

author: TAPAN SUSHEEL
description: Abdul Aleem Ansari, an assistant professor, has been arrested for allegedly molesting around 12 undergraduate women during a physics practical examination at KLDAV PG College in Roorkee. The victims reported inappropriate touching and harassment during viva voce tests in a closed room.
title: Roorkee professor ‘molests’ 12 college students during viva

author: TNN
title: Mumbai airport, Taj Mahal Palace receive bomb threat

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A Russian drone strike on a civilian bus in Ukraine's Sumy region resulted in at least nine fatalities and four injuries, according to local authorities. The Sumy regional military administration condemned the attack near Bilopillya as a "cynical attack" on civilians.
title: Russia strikes Ukraine civilian bus, 9 killed

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Amidst political dynamics, Congress nominated four leaders for an all-party delegation, excluding Shashi Tharoor, despite his selection to lead the Operation Sindoor briefing. Jairam Ramesh shared the Congress's nominees, while Union Minister Kiren Rijiju emphasized national unity by including Tharoor in a separate delegation to convey India's firm stance against terrorism to key partner nations.
title: Tharoor chosen to lead all-party delegation despite name missing from Congress list

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Air India is urging Indian authorities to block IndiGo's leasing agreement with Turkish Airlines, citing business disadvantages and security concerns related to Turkey's stance on Pakistan.
title: Air India lobbies govt to stop IndiGo lease with Turkish Airlines

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: During the Sagarmatha Sambaad in Nepal, China's Vice Chairman Xiao Jie repeatedly referred to Mount Everest as "Chomolungma," the Chinese name, while other participants used English and Nepali designations. Despite Prime Minister Oli's advocacy for "Sagarmatha," he remained silent on Xiao Jie's terminology. The event, attended by international delegations and organizations, highlighted differing perspectives on the iconic peak's naming.
title: Chinese leader refers to Mount Everest as ‘Chomolungma’ at Nepal forum

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Karun Nair's impressive Ranji Trophy performance has earned him a spot in the India ‘A’ squad for the England tour, reigniting hopes for a national team comeback. Alongside Nair, Abhimanyu Easwaran will lead a team featuring experienced players and promising uncapped talents.
title: 'Dear cricket will ... ': Irfan Pathan's post for Karun Nair sparks buzz

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Elon Musk, the tech magnate, has once again altered his Twitter (X) profile name, this time to Kekius Maximus, following a previous change to Gorklon Rust. This playful alteration coincides with a profile picture update featuring Musk in armor, emblazoned with "Emperor Kekius Maximus.
title: Elon Musk changes his name on Twitter again, this time he returns as…

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Following the Pahalgam terrorist incident, India has intensified scrutiny of imports from the UAE, Iran, and other Gulf nations to prevent Pakistani goods from entering indirectly. A complete ban on Pakistani goods is now in effect, with strict verification of import labels and origin criteria.
title: How India is preventing entry of Pakistan goods from Gulf countries

author: KAPIL DIXIT
description: Cash rained down at Jaiswal Dhaba on the Prayagraj-Kanpur highway. A thief tried to steal businessman Bhavesh Kumar Barot's bag. The bag burst open, scattering Rs 5.65 lakh. People initially grabbed the cash. Police and dhaba staff appealed for its return. Everyone returned the money. Police filed a case against the thief. Barot thanked everyone for their honesty.
title: Money Heist: When cash ‘rained’ at UP dhaba after thief tried to snatch bizman’s bag

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: NIA apprehended two ISIS fugitives, Abdullah Faiyaz Shaikh and Talha Khan, at Mumbai airport upon their return from Jakarta. They were wanted in connection with a 2023 Pune IED case. The suspects, who had evaded capture for two years, are accused of plotting to destabilize India and establish Islamic rule, having assembled and tested IEDs in Pune.
title: NIA arrests two ISIS sleeper cell fugitives at Mumbai airport in 2023 IED Case

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Following Operation Sindoor, India is dispatching all-party parliamentary delegations to key global capitals to present a united front against Pakistan-sponsored terrorism. Led by senior MPs, these delegations will raise awareness about cross-border terrorism and explain India's rationale behind the strikes. The initiative aims to showcase India’s bipartisan resolve and zero-tolerance approach to terrorism on international platforms.
title: Op Sindoor briefing: 7 MPs to lead all-party delegations to US, UK, Japan

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Rohit Sharma, visibly emotional, honoured his parents at Wankhede Stadium during the unveiling of a stand named after him on Friday. He expressed gratitude for their sacrifices, acknowledging their role in his cricketing journey. Alongside Sharma, Ajit Wadekar and Sharad Pawar were also recognised.
title: Rohit Sharma stand: MCA hands first ticket to former Test captain

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: World Hypertension Day, observed on May 17th, raises awareness about high blood pressure and its consequences. Managing hypertension involves lifestyle changes like the DASH diet, which emphasizes fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and low-fat dairy while limiting sodium and unhealthy fats. This diet effectively lowers blood pressure, reduces heart disease risk, and improves overall health.
title: World Hypertension Day 2025: All about the DASH diet to keep stress at bay

author: BHARAT YAGNIK
description: In Ahmedabad, Dipesh Kevlani cleared CAT after his brother Dinesh completed IIM Lucknow. Dipesh, a watchman, supported his family and now seeks a loan for IIM Shillong. Suraj Soni, son of a peon and domestic help, also received an IIM Shillong offer. He studied in Gujarati medium and awaits loan approval. Both youths hope their education will uplift their families.
title: Ahmedabad watchman waits for brother’s MBA, cracks CAT, gets IIM call

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Donald Trump claimed that India and Pakistan were dangerously close to a nuclear conflict following the Pahalgam terror attack and India's Operation Sindoor. He stated that the situation escalated rapidly with increasing missile threats, emphasizing the potential for nuclear war.
title: 'Bigger success': Trump says he made peace between India and Pak at brink of 'N-word'

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Donald Trump praised Iranian drone technology for its affordability and effectiveness, contrasting its low cost with the high prices quoted by US defense manufacturers. He highlighted the deadly impact of drones in modern warfare, referencing their use in conflicts like the Russia-Ukraine war.
title: '$40,000 vs $41 mn': Trump praises Iranian drones for being 'good, fast and deadly'

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Moody's Ratings has lowered the United States government's credit rating. This is due to concerns about increasing government debt. The downgrade creates problems for President Trump.
title: Blow to Trump? Moody's strips US of top credit rating

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: The FDA has cleared the Lumipulse G pTau217/β-Amyloid 1-42 Plasma Ratio test, the first blood test for early Alzheimer's detection in adults aged 55 and older showing symptoms. It analyzes pTau217 and beta-amyloid ratios, correlating with brain amyloid plaques. This advancement offers a more accessible and cost-effective alternative to PET scans, potentially enabling earlier intervention and treatment.
title: FDA greenlights blood test for Alzheimer’s disease: How does it work?

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Neeraj Chopra made history at the Doha Diamond League 2025, becoming the first Indian to breach the 90-meter mark with a 90.23m throw. Despite this personal best, he secured second place, with Germany's Julian Weber winning at 91.06m. PM Narendra Modi lauded Chopra's achievement as a moment of national pride, acknowledging his dedication.
title: 'India is elated and proud': PM Modi lauds Neeraj on breaching 90m mark

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Reports surfaced that the Trump administration explored a plan to relocate up to 1 million Palestinians from Gaza to Libya, potentially using unfrozen Libyan funds as compensation. However, the State Department refuted these claims, deeming the situation in Libya unsuitable.
title: Is Trump administration planning to move 1 million Palestinians to Libya?

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: King Charles III's personal wealth has surged to an estimated £640 million, surpassing that of his mother, Queen Elizabeth II, due to inherited investments and estates. This increase places him on par with Rishi Sunak and Akshata Murty, despite their wealth slightly decreasing.
title: King Charles III is now richer than Queen Elizabeth II: But how did this happen?

author: AHMED ALI
description: In a tragic incident early Friday, Punit Singh Majra, 28, died after crashing his rented BMW X1 into a dumper on the Atal Setu in Mumbai. Driving at a speed of 180 kmph, Majra lost control of the vehicle. Police extracted his body from the wreckage and transported him to a hospital, where he was declared dead.
title: Mumbai's Atal Setu: 28-year-old driving BMW dies after crashing into dumper

author: SOUMITRA BOSE
description: Sunita, a 43-year-old Nagpur woman, has crossed the Line of Control into Pakistan, baffling Indian security agencies. Driven by a desire to meet a Pakistani pastor she met online, this was her third attempt to cross the border. She left her son in Kargil before crossing over and is now believed to be in Pakistani custody.
title: Nagpur woman on vacation crossed into Pakistan ‘to meet pastor she met online’

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The Congress party lauded the Centre's decision to appoint Shashi Tharoor to lead a delegation of MPs to expose Pakistan-sponsored terrorism on international platforms, citing a perceived "talent vacuum" within the BJP.
title: 'Talent vacuum in BJP': Cong on Tharoor leading delegation to expose Pak's terrorism

author: ANJALI SINGH
description: Following the declaration of class 12 board exam results, eighteen government schools in Haryana have come under scrutiny due to a zero percent pass rate. These schools are among 100 poorly performing institutions that have overshadowed the state's overall pass percentage.
title: 'Teachers overburdened': 18 govt schools in Haryana record zero passes in 12th boards

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: In a brazen jailbreak, ten inmates escaped the Orleans Justice Center in New Orleans after exploiting a hole behind a toilet. The absence of a guard and suspected insider assistance facilitated the escape. Two fugitives have been apprehended, while eight remain at large, considered armed and dangerous. Authorities are investigating security failures and urging public vigilance as the search intensifies.
title: ‘To easy lol’: 10 inmates use blankets to escape through hole in New Orleans jail

author: TNN
description: In Prayagraj, a three-and-a-half-year-old nursery student tragically died after allegedly being slapped by teachers at his private school. Police have registered an FIR against the teachers for culpable homicide, following allegations of physical and emotional distress inflicted upon the child.
title: UP nursery student dies after being slapped for crying

author: SUGANDHA JHA
description: Jawaharlal Nehru University (JNU) has issued eviction notices to 232 final-year students, requiring them to vacate hostel rooms by May 31, raising concerns about thesis submissions and final exams.
title: JNU asks 232 final year students to vacate hostel rooms by May 31, triggers concern

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Ravi Shastri suggests grooming Shubman Gill or Rishabh Pant as India's next Test captain, following Rohit Sharma's retirement. He advises against burdening Jasprit Bumrah with captaincy due to injury concerns. Shastri emphasizes the importance of age and longevity, highlighting Gill and Pant's leadership experience in the IPL. He dismisses concerns about Gill's overseas performance, backing his potential for future success.
title: 'Don't make Jasprit Bumrah captain': Ravi Shastri drops bombshell

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: President Trump claimed India offered to eliminate all tariffs for the U.S., but he's in no rush to finalize a trade deal. This follows India's aim to secure an agreement during a tariff suspension period. Bilateral trade between the two nations reached $129 billion in 2024, with India holding a $45.7 billion surplus.
title: 'I’m in no rush': Trump says India willing to cut 100% tariffs for US

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: An emotional Rohit Sharma, alongside his family, unveiled the 'Rohit Sharma Stand' at Wankhede Stadium, a tribute to his parents' sacrifices. He shared a light moment with a fan and expressed gratitude to his family during the Mumbai Cricket Association ceremony. Rohit’s wife, Ritika, stood proudly by his side, her beaming smile reflecting the pride of the occasion.
title: Rohit Sharma pretends to punch fan at Wankhede Stadium - WATCH

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: Watch: Albanian PM puts aside his umbrella, kneels in front of Meloni in Turin

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Pakistani Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif revealed that Indian ballistic missiles struck Nur Khan Airbase and other locations, prompting a late-night call from the Army Chief. India initiated Operation Sindoor following a terror attack, targeting terror infrastructure and militants. Hostilities ceased on May 10 after retaliatory actions and coordinated attacks on Pakistani airbases.
title: Watch: In a first, Pakistan PM admits India hit Nur Khan Airbase

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Following Turkey's support for Pakistan during a recent military conflict, Myntra and Ajio have reportedly stopped selling Turkish apparel brands. According to Reliance, this decision aligns with national sentiment, prompting reassessments of partnerships and the closure of Reliance's Turkey office. Traders' body CAIT has also called for a complete boycott of trade with Turkey and Azerbaijan, urging policy reviews and discouraging business engagements.

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Neeraj Chopra achieved a personal best of 90.23m at the Doha Diamond League, finally crossing the 90m threshold, but finished second to Germany's Julian Weber, who threw 91.06m. Despite the 'bitter-sweet' result, Chopra is optimistic, crediting his coach Jan Zelezny and feeling fitter after groin issues. Chopra credited the favourable conditions in Doha for helping him unleash the big throw and shared that Zelezny had predicted a 90m effort even before the competition.

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Rohit Sharma was overcome with emotion at Wankhede Stadium as a stand was unveiled in his name, a tribute to his illustrious career. He expressed gratitude to his parents for their sacrifices and shared the honor with legends Ajit Wadekar and Sharad Pawar. Ritika Sajdeh, Rohit's wife, stood beside him, smiling proudly as she soaked in the emotional moment.
title: 'I wanted to play ... ': Rohit Sharma's emotional confession

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: The Wankhede Stadium honored Rohit Sharma with the unveiling of the 'Rohit Sharma Stand.' An emotional Rohit expressed gratitude to his family and fans, reflecting on his journey since 2007. A lighthearted moment, capturing Rohit playfully teasing his brother about a car dent, went viral. He acknowledged the stadium's significance and looked forward to playing for Mumbai Indians there.
title: 'Yeh kya hai?': Rohit Sharma loses cool, scolds brother for denting his car

author: TNN
description: In a tragic incident in Varanasi, a 26-year-old woman, Aarti Pal, was allegedly beaten to death by her husband, Raju Pal, just a week after their wedding. Police arrested Raju, who has a history of failed marriages, following a domestic dispute at Amouli village. Aarti's family alerted the authorities after Raju informed them of the assault.
title: Newly married man beats wife to death with sticks in UP

author: HRUSHIKESH MOHANTY
description: In a shocking turn of events, a young girl in Gajapati district has been detained for allegedly killing her adoptive mother, who disapproved of her relationships with two older men. The girl, along with her two boyfriends, are accused of smothering the woman with a pillow.
title: She was 3 days old when a woman took her in. At 14, she killed her with 2 boyfriends

author: TNN
description: Chandrabhan Dubey, a security agency owner, was found murdered and his body was discovered in two bags in Surat's Althan area. Police investigations revealed that Rashid Ansari, Dubey's employee, allegedly kidnapped and killed him for a ransom of Rs 1 crore.
title: Gujarat horror: Businessman chopped into pieces, stuffed into two bags by employee

author: TIFFANY MAY
description: Fu Zai, a corgi with a remarkable sense of smell, has become a social media sensation as a sniffer dog for the Weifang Public Security Bureau in China. Despite his success in detecting explosives and fitting into tight spaces, Fu Zai's love for treats has led to some amusing incidents, including snatching a sausage from a child.
title: China’s first police Corgi has 400,000 followers and a nose for trouble

author: PANKAJ DOVAL
description: Hyundai plans a major India expansion. The company will launch 26 new cars in the next five years. This includes electric, hybrid, and petrol models. Hyundai will invest Rs 7,000 crore. The company aims for a bigger market share. They are focusing on profits, not discount wars. Eight new models are expected by FY27.
title: Hyundai lines up new models to regain ground

author: TNN
description: Dalal Street witnessed a significant rally following the Indo-Pak ceasefire, adding over $300 billion to investor wealth. The Sensex and Nifty climbed, fueled by foreign and domestic fund inflows, a fall in retail inflation, and expectations of RBI rate cuts. Smallcap and midcap stocks outperformed, with defense and railway sectors experiencing substantial gains.
title: Relief rally: Sensex soars 3,000 points in week
